FBIS3-43943 "drafr014_c_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Justice Minister, PAC Holding Talks in Pretoria MB2001145294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 20 Jan 94 MB2001145294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Ministry of Defense has confirmed that Minister Kobie Coetsee is engaged in talks with a PAC [Pan-Africanist Congress] delegation in Pretoria. Earlier the PAC said that members of its Executive Committee, including Mr. Benny Alexander and Mr. Barney Desai, were to have talks with the government today. The talks follow the PAC's announcement that it has suspended its armed struggle. The agenda for today's talks is expected to include possible amnesty for APLA [Azanian People's Liberation Army -- PAC military wing] members, joint command of the security forces, and PAC participation in the Transitional Executive Council.
